              },
              "free_text": [
                " PD-300 Neutron Generator"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Three pellets, about 0.15 cm thick and 20 mm in",
                "diameter were formed by pressing approximately 10",
                "gram of Eu2O3 (99.99% pure) powder (natural isotopic",
                "composition) at 980 MPa to form a pellet. The samples",
                "were irradiated in contact with the target and",
                "sandwiched between two standard Al foils (99.999%",
                "pure, 0.3 mm thick) of the same diameter used to",
                "monitor the neutron fluence via the 27Al(n,a)24Na",
                "reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A 2.40 mg/cm2 thick tritium-titanium (T-Ti)",
                "target at a distance of about 5 cm. Neutrons were",
                "produced with an effective deuteron beam energy of",
                "125 keV and beam current of 200 uA."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A high-purity germanium detector (ORTEC, model",
                "GEM 60P, crystal diameter: 70.1 mm, crystal length:",
                "72.3 mm) with a relative efficiency of about 68% and",
                "an energy resolution of 1.69 keV at 1.332 MeV for",
                "60Co. The efficiency of the detector was",
                "pre-calibrated using the standard gamma sources 54Mn,",
                "57Co, 60Co, 109Cd, 133Ba, 137Cs, 152Eu, 241Am and",
                "226Ra."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Irradiation of the samples was lasted",
                "approximately 2 hours with a yield about 3-4E10",
                "n/(4pi*s). The groups of samples were placed at 0, 90",
                "and 135 degree relative to the beam direction."
              ]
            }
          ],
